# Quick Start Commands

See [STARTUP_GUIDE.md](mdc:STARTUP_GUIDE.md) for full details.

## Running Services

### Terminal 1: BuidlGuidl Frontend (port 3000)
```bash
cd eth-ai-asa
yarn install
yarn start
```

### Terminal 2: ElizaOS Agents (port 3001)
```bash
cd agent-marketplace
bun install
# Verify .env has SERVER_PORT=3001
bun run start
# or: elizaos start
```

### Terminal 3: XMTP Agent
```bash
cd xmtp-agent
bun install
# Verify .env has XMTP_WALLET_KEY, XMTP_DB_ENCRYPTION_KEY
bun run dev
```

## Testing Agent Endpoints
```bash
# DeFi Wizard
curl -X POST http://localhost:3001/api/agents/defi-wizard/message \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"message": "What is yield farming?"}'

# Security Guru
curl -X POST http://localhost:3001/api/agents/security-guru/message \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"message": "What are reentrancy attacks?"}'
```

## Port Reference
- 3000: BuidlGuidl frontend
- 3001: ElizaOS agents server
- 5173: Vite dev server (if running from agent-marketplace)
- XMTP: Uses websocket (configured in .env)